{
    "name": "Brood Leech Swarm",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Brood Leech Swarm",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Most smaller species of leeches do not tend to swarm, but brood leeches are prone to gathering in seething, undulant mats of squirming gluttony. When they gather in sufficient numbers to swarm, they eschew the stealth of a lone leech's feeding methods in favor of swift and merciless feeding. In these situations, their mild venom can affect much larger creatures than their usual prey.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Animal</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a></u>)</b>: DC 19",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Bestiary 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 156",
                        "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 156",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                    },
                    "page": 156
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Leech",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Leech Species",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "The spotted hooktooth leech is often found in areas frequented by trolls, who sometimes wear them as awful decorations, relying on their regeneration to control the bleeding effects. The gigantic elephant leech feeds on immense beasts of the swamplands or jungles, like <a aonid=\"125\" game-obj=\"MonsterFamilies\">elephants</a>, <a aonid=\"676\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">froghemoths</a>, and <a aonid=\"32\" game-obj=\"MonsterFamilies\">dinosaurs</a>, attacking from unexpected range. But it's the relatively small gutleech that provides the most fuel for nightmares, due to its awful habit of feeding on victims from inside.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Bestiary 2",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 156",
                                "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 156",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                            },
                            "page": 156
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "related_creatures",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Related Creatures",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Related Creatures",
                        "image": "Sidebar_4_RelatedCreatures.png"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "text": "Though valued by apothecaries and field medics as methods to reduce swelling or drain blood, leeches are despised by most who encounter them, regardless of the setting.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Bestiary 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 156",
                        "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 156",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                    },
                    "page": 156
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
